<p>Using Python, how can I take a string with an unformatted link like this:</p>  <pre><code>str = "&lt;p&gt;Here's some safe html with a link to somewhere: \ https://google.ca but there might also be some images &lt;img \ src='https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Man-in-circle_icon.svg' /&gt; \ and other linky looking things&lt;/p&gt;" </code></pre>  <p>And wrap it in  tags like this:</p>  <pre><code>str = "&lt;p&gt;Here's some safe html with a link to somewhere: \ &lt;a href='https://google.ca' target='_blank'&gt;https://google.ca&lt;/a&gt; but there might also be some images &lt;img \ src='https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Man-in-circle_icon.svg' /&gt; \ and other linky looking things&lt;/p&gt;" </code></pre>